library(ggplot2)
ggplot() +
  geom_line(data = earners.income, aes(x = earners, y = income)) +
  geom_line(data = data.frame(x = c(0, 100), y = c(0, 100)), aes(x = x, y = y)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = c(0, 100), linetype = "dotted") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(0, 100), linetype = "dotted") + 
  geom_polygon(data = earners.income, aes(x = earners, y = income), alpha = 0.5, fill = "grey") +
  geom_point(data = earners.income, aes(x = earners, y = income), shape = 21, fill = "white", size = 3) +
  ggtitle("Lorenz Curve of Korea Income") + xlab("Earners Cumulated (%)") + ylab("Income Cumulated (%)") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = earners[c(1:8, 14)], labels = earners[c(1:8, 14)]) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 100, by = 25)) +
  annotate("text", x = 30, y = 60, label = "Gini = 0.501", size = 7) +
  theme_bw()
